\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120\sl480\slmult0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
On 28 August 2000 the Competition Tribunal, acting in terms of section 59(1) of the Competition Act, 89 of 1998 ("the Act"), granted an order of interim relief to the 5th to 13th respondents against appellants, of whom the 1st to 5th appellants are pharmaceutical manufacturers and importers who have established a joint exclusive distribution agreement for their products, the 6th appellant is a company formed by these manufacturers to establish a distribution agency and the 7th appellant is the distribution agency.}
\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120\sl480\slmult0\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi720{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
In granting an order the Tribunal justified its decision thus:}
\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120\sl480\slmult0\li1440\ri0\lin1440\rin0\fi0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
"We find that an interim order is necessary in this case to prevent the purposes of the Act from being frustrated. The main purpose of the Act is to promote and maintain competition. The effect of the prohibited practice found in this case is to lessen competition in the distribution of pharmaceutical products. It is our view that it is reasonably necessary for us to give the interim relief order, as failure to do so will be allow (sic) the continuous frustration of the purposes of the Act. If we do not grant the interim order and the claimants subsequently get a final order the competitive process and structure for the distribution of the respondents' manufacturers products will have been so skewed in favour of DD (7th appellant in the present appeal) and the respondents, that a final order may not be able to adequately address the effects of DD's conversion on the nature of competition in the distribution market."}
\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120\sl480\slmult0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
\tab Accordingly the Tribunal made the following order:}
\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120\sl480\slmult0\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
1.   \tab The claimants' application for interim relief in terms of section 59 of the Competition Act 89 0f 1998 is granted in respect of the respondents' alleged contraventions of section 4(1)(a) of the Act.}
\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120{\listtext\pard\plain  2.\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360{\rtlch \ltrch\fs24
      }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
Respondents supply their products directly to the claimants and other wholesalers on term and conditions similar to those that apply to transactions between them and the claimants  and other }
\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\fs24
      }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
wholesalers immediately before the conversion of DD to a joint exclusive distribution agency for their products.}
\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120{\listtext\pard\plain  3.\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360{\rtlch \ltrch\fs24
      }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
The order is to remain in force until the earlier of ; }
\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120{\listtext\pard\plain  (i)\tab}\ilvl0\ls2 \li1440\ri0\lin1440\rin0\fi-360\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
conclusion of the hearing into the prohibited practices alleged by the claimants to have been committed by the respondents; or}
\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120\sl480\slmult0\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
