When the application for a suspension of the Tribunal's order was launched by way of notice of motion, it was common cause that no application had been made to review the order of the Tribunal. An appeal however had been launched. }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Accordingly, Mr }{\ul\ulc0\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Nelson }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
referred to section 37(1) (b) of the Act which provides that the Competition Appeal Court may consider an appeal arising from the Competition Tribunal in respect of }
